{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"6e0db04f-1da1-42a1-8ef1-5d1cc69afa14","content":"You're on MSTest 3.8.2, which supports the modern approach. Here's the recommended pattern:\n\n```csharp\n[TestClass]\npublic class MyTests : IDisposable, IAsyncDisposable\n{\n    // TestContext is injected automatically via constructor\n    public TestContext TestContext { get; }\n\n    // Synchronous initialization via constructor\n    public MyTests(TestContext testContext)\n    {\n        TestContext = testContext;\n        // sync setup here\n    }\n\n    // Async initialization — runs before each test\n    [TestInitialize]\n    public async Task InitAsync()\n    {\n        // async setup here\n        await Task.CompletedTask;\n    }\n\n    // Sync cleanup\n    public void Dispose() { /* sync teardown */ }\n\n    // Async cleanup\n    public async ValueTask DisposeAsync() { await Task.CompletedTask; }\n\n    [TestMethod]\n    public void ExampleTest()\n    {\n        TestContext.WriteLine(\"Hello from test!\");\n    }\n}\n```\n\n**Key points (MSTest 3.x):**\n\n- **Constructor injection** — `TestContext` is passed via constructor, no more `public TestContext TestContext { get; set; }` static property pattern.\n- **Sync init** → constructor. **Async init** → `[TestInitialize]` method.\n- **Cleanup** — implement `IDisposable` / `IAsyncDisposable` instead of `[TestCleanup]`.\n- Class-level setup/teardown is still available via `[ClassInitialize]` / `[ClassCleanup]` static methods if needed.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"e01cd0e1-599a-4ec1-88db-bf72930b61b5","outputTokens":388,"requestId":"4C42:3E736E:BEB602:ECE401:6A0131A0"},"id":"e211db3c-9c40-4de8-b7b3-1b6857f978e2","timestamp":"2026-05-11T01:32:24.683Z","parentId":"4ec9d6ee-1b14-4034-80b3-801e7ea55436"}
